{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/diskinjector"]}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before the VM boots, ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiskInjector","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" mounts the guest disk image on the host,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"writes a standard macOS LaunchDaemon plist and the user’s script to the data","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"volume, then unmounts. When the VM boots, ","type":"text"},{"code":"launchd","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" picks up the daemon and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"executes the script automatically — no SSH, no agent, no network required.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This uses Apple’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (ships with macOS) to attach APFS disk images","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and writes only to the data volume (never the Signed System Volume).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Usage","level":2,"text":"Usage","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let scriptURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"\/path\/to\/setup.sh\")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","try DiskInjector.inject(script: scriptURL, into: bundle)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"How-It-Works","level":2,"text":"How It Works","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attaches the guest’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"type":"text","text":" using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":" without mounting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(to discover the device node)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds and mounts the APFS data volume from the attached disk."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the user’s script to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/usr\/local\/bin\/spooktacular-user-data.sh"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the data volume."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes a LaunchDaemon plist to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/"},{"type":"text","text":" that tells"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"type":"text","text":" to run the script at boot."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Detaches the disk image so the VM can boot cleanly."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"anchor":"Thread-Safety","level":2,"text":"Thread Safety","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All methods are synchronous and use ","type":"text"},{"code":"Process","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to invoke ","type":"text"},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Call from a background thread if needed to avoid blocking the main thread.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"symbolKind":"enum","roleHeading":"Enumeration","title":"DiskInjector","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit12DiskInjectorO"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/Spooktacu